## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- MySQL 8+ (or Docker)

### 1. Clone & Install

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
cd telecom-billing-system
npm install
```

### 2. Configure Environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your database credentials and JWT secret
```

Required variables:
```
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_password
DB_DATABASE=telecomdb
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
```

### 3. Run with Docker (Recommended)

```bash
docker-compose up
```

This starts both the app (port 3000) and MySQL (port 8889). Tables are auto-created on first boot.

### 4. Run Locally (Without Docker)

```bash
npm run dev        # Development with hot-reload
npm run build      # Compile TypeScript
npm start          # Production mode
```

### 5. Open API Docs

Navigate to `http://localhost:3000/api-docs` for the interactive Swagger UI.

---

## API Overview

| Method | Route | Auth | Description |
|--------|-------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/users/signup` | — | Register a new user |
| `POST` | `/users/login` | — | Authenticate and get JWT |
| `GET`  | `/users/profile/:id` | JWT | Get user profile |
| `POST` | `/usage/calls` | JWT | Log call duration (CDR) |
| `POST` | `/usage/sms` | JWT | Log SMS count (CDR) |
| `POST` | `/usage/data` | JWT | Log data usage in MB (CDR) |
| `POST` | `/billing/generate/:userId` | JWT | Generate bill for billing period |
| `GET`  | `/billing/user/:userId` | JWT | List bills (paginated, filterable) |
| `POST` | `/billing/pay` | JWT | Mark bill as paid |
| `GET`  | `/billing/:billId` | JWT | Get bill details |
| `GET`  | `/billing/ledger/:userId` | JWT | Audit trail — every charge/payment |
| `GET`  | `/billing/search` | JWT | Search bills (date range, amount, status) |
| `GET`  | `/billing/reconcile/:userId` | JWT + Admin | Verify ledger integrity (prove every cent) |
| `GET`  | `/billing/dlq` | JWT + Admin | View failed CDRs (Dead Letter Queue) |
| `PUT`  | `/billing/dlq/:id/resolve` | JWT + Admin | Mark DLQ item as resolved |
| `PUT`  | `/billing/dlq/:id/discard` | JWT + Admin | Discard invalid DLQ item |
| `PUT`  | `/rates/:service` | JWT + API Key | Update service rate (admin) |
| `GET`  | `/rates/:service` | JWT + API Key | Get service rates (admin) |

### Example: Log a Call with Idempotency

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/usage/calls \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "userId": 1,
    "duration": 300,
    "idempotencyKey": "call-2026-04-19-abc123"
  }'
```

